Topic: Knowledge check

Link: https://www.theodinproject.com/lessons/foundations-introduction-to-html-and-css#knowledge-check


Knowledge check

1. What do HTML and CSS stand for?
HTML is Hyper text Markup language, is a markup language that is used to structure the information on the document.

CSS Cascade style sheet, is a design languange, used to give style to the document.

2. Between HTML and CSS, which would you use for putting paragraphs of text on a webpage?
HTML p tags ex: <p>Text inside</p>

3. Between HTML and CSS, which would you use for changing the font and background color of a button?
CSS
.classButton {
    background-color: red;
    color: white;
}

4. What is the difference between HTML, CSS and JavaScript?

- HTML is used mainly to structure the document
- CSS is used to mainly to give style to the document.
- JavaScript is used to give logic and responsivenes to the document.